# Why use a framework?

## Security

* CSRF: a token is added to a form and checked when the form is submitted
* SQL Injection: Slick prevent it
* XSS: Twirl templating engine escape all dynamic values displayed to the user

## Code organisation

### Views

* Main template contains the common code
* each route has a specific view included in the main template
* each view can append specific javascript

### URL

* route define good looking URLs
* easy to define parameters

## Form

* Validation
 * built-in
 * custom
* Form templating with bootstrap
* Display error automatically
* GET - POST - Redirect to avoid multiple form submission


## DB

* Slick is just fucking amazing
* Migrations

## I18N

